<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/"><channel><title>DutchNews.nl</title><link>https://www.dutchnews.nl/</link><description>DutchNews.nl brings daily news from The Netherlands in English</description><lastBuildDate>Mon, 09 Sep 2024 08:13:17 +0000</lastBuildDate><item><title>Dutch Game Garden to close down after subsidy shift</title><link>https://www.dutchnews.nl/2024/09/dutch-game-garden-to-close-down-after-subsidy-shift/</link><description><![CDATA[<article class="post-240557 post type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-business category-economy category-tech"><header class="pb-4 px-4"><h1 class="text-serif lh-1"> Dutch Game Garden to close down after subsidy shift</h1> <time class="text-secondary updated me-2" datetime="2024-09-09T08:13:17+00:00"> September 9, 2024 </time></header><figure aria-describedby="caption-attachment-240558" class="px-lg-5" id="attachment_240558"> <img alt="" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" decoding="async" fetchpriority="high" height="563" sizes="(max-width: 718px) 100vw, 718px" src="/wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/Depositphotos_408905654_S-e1725869561688.jpg" srcset="/wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/Depositphotos_408905654_S-e1725869561688.jpg 718w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/Depositphotos_408905654_S-e1725869561688-560x439.jpg 560w" width="718"/><figcaption class="px-4 px-lg-0" id="caption-attachment-240558"> Photo: Depositphotos.com</figcaption></figure><main class="px-4"><p>The Dutch Game Garden, a hub for the Dutch computer games industry in Utrecht, is closing down at the end of this year, following a change in the subsidy set up.</p><p>The decision means the Netherlands is losing a “pillar” of the games industry, Martine Spaans, director of the Dutch Games Association told news agency ANP. “The DGG was the first place that people starting a studio would come to. It was home to a wealth of expertise.”</p><p>The province funded the DGG but has changed the conditions attached to its subsidies and the DGG said it <a href="https://www.dutchgamegarden.nl/dutch-game-garden-to-close-its-doors/">could not work</a> within the new set-up. “Unfortunately, we have been forced to close our doors,” said chairman Peter Laanen. “But we can look back with pride at all we have achieved in the past 17 years.”</p><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden p-4 bg-light my-8 d-none d-md-block"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Inarticle"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_inarticle" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden p-4 bg-light my-8 d-block d-md-none"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Inarticle"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_inarticle-m" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><p>Some 4,500 people work in the Dutch games industry and 130 companies have gone through the DGG’s incubator programme since its inception in 2008.</p><p>Several of the companies which started out under the DGG umbrella have broken through internationally, such as Abbey Games, Ronimo Games and Vlambeer. As well as entertainment games, DGG companies were involved in educational and medical gaming.</p><p>According <a href="https://www.nrc.nl/nieuws/2024/09/06/koepelorganisatie-dutch-game-garden-stopt-een-klap-voor-de-nederlandse-game-industrie-a4864810">to the NRC</a>, the DGG was given €700,000 by the city council and €250,000 by the province last year. The DGG did not say how much cash it was losing but did say it could not put together a responsible budget.</p></main><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden d-none d-md-block p-4 bg-light mt-8 mb-10 mx-lg-4"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Native"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_native" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden d-block d-md-none bg-light my-8"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Native"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_native-m" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><footer class="my-8 px-4"><div class="pb-8"></div> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/business/?list"></a> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/economy/?list"></a> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/tech/?list"></a></footer><div class="bg-green-light p-3 mx-4 mt-8 mb-12"></div></article>]]></description><guid>https://www.dutchnews.nl/?p=240557</guid><pubDate>Mon, 09 Sep 2024 08:13:17 -0000</pubDate><dc:creator><![CDATA[Robin Pascoe]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Sumatran tiger dies after fight in captive breeding programme</title><link>https://www.dutchnews.nl/2024/09/sumatran-tiger-dies-after-fight-in-captive-breeding-programme/</link><description><![CDATA[<article class="post-240550 post type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-animal-welfare category-society"><header class="pb-4 px-4"><h1 class="text-serif lh-1"> Sumatran tiger dies after fight in captive breeding programme</h1> <time class="text-secondary updated me-2" datetime="2024-09-09T07:39:09+00:00"> September 9, 2024 </time></header><figure aria-describedby="caption-attachment-240552" class="px-lg-5" id="attachment_240552"> <img alt="" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" decoding="async" fetchpriority="high" height="667" sizes="(max-width: 1000px) 100vw, 1000px" src="/wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/Depositphotos_490721546_S.jpg" srcset="/wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/Depositphotos_490721546_S.jpg 1000w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/Depositphotos_490721546_S-560x374.jpg 560w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/Depositphotos_490721546_S-360x240.jpg 360w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/Depositphotos_490721546_S-768x512.jpg 768w" width="1000"/><figcaption class="px-4 px-lg-0" id="caption-attachment-240552"> A Sumatran tiger (Panthera tigris sumatrae). Photo: Depositphotos.com</figcaption></figure><main class="px-4"><p>Efforts to get two new tigers at Blijdorp zoo in Rotterdam to mate as part of a captive breeding programme have ended in tragedy, after a fight in which the female tiger died.</p><p>The tiger, known as Nonja, was found dead in the tiger enclosure on Friday morning. She had arrived in the zoo in June, three weeks after the Sumatran male Geram.</p><p>The two tigers were placed in the same enclosure on Thursday after Nonja appeared to be in heat. “That meeting ended in a fight,” the zoo said in a statement. “The zoo keepers eventually managed to separate the two animals.”</p><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden p-4 bg-light my-8 d-none d-md-block"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Inarticle"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_inarticle" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden p-4 bg-light my-8 d-block d-md-none"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Inarticle"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_inarticle-m" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><p>An autopsy at Utrecht University’s faculty of veterinary medicine showed Nonja had been killed by bleeding on one of her lungs, probably caused by a bite. The injury had not been visible through her thick coat, the zoo said.</p><p>There are just 350 Sumatran tigers, which live a solitary existence, in the wild.</p><p>The zoo said it did not yet know what impact the death would have on any future attempts to breed Sumatran tigers in Blijdorp.</p></main><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden d-none d-md-block p-4 bg-light mt-8 mb-10 mx-lg-4"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Native"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_native" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden d-block d-md-none bg-light my-8"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Native"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_native-m" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><footer class="my-8 px-4"><div class="pb-8"></div> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/animal-welfare/?list"></a> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/society/?list"></a></footer><div class="bg-green-light p-3 mx-4 mt-8 mb-12"></div></article>]]></description><guid>https://www.dutchnews.nl/?p=240550</guid><pubDate>Mon, 09 Sep 2024 07:39:09 -0000</pubDate><dc:creator><![CDATA[Robin Pascoe]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Union membership shrinks to 15% of the workforce in NL</title><link>https://www.dutchnews.nl/2024/09/union-membership-shrinks-to-15-of-the-workforce-in-nl/</link><description><![CDATA[<article class="post-240547 post type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-uncategorized"><header class="pb-4 px-4"><h1 class="text-serif lh-1"> Union membership shrinks to 15% of the workforce in NL</h1> <time class="text-secondary updated me-2" datetime="2024-09-09T07:04:58+00:00"> September 9, 2024 </time></header><figure aria-describedby="caption-attachment-140119" class="px-lg-5" id="attachment_140119"> <img alt="" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" decoding="async" fetchpriority="high" height="821" sizes="(max-width: 1093px) 100vw, 1093px" src="/wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/fnv-pensions-agreement.jpg" srcset="/wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/fnv-pensions-agreement.jpg 1093w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/fnv-pensions-agreement-560x421.jpg 560w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/fnv-pensions-agreement-768x577.jpg 768w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/fnv-pensions-agreement-640x481.jpg 640w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/fnv-pensions-agreement-93x70.jpg 93w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/fnv-pensions-agreement-130x98.jpg 130w" width="1093"/><figcaption class="px-4 px-lg-0" id="caption-attachment-140119"> Photo: DutchNews.nl</figcaption></figure><main class="px-4"><p><span data-preserver-spaces="true">Just 15% of the Dutch workforce are members of a trade union, down three percentage points </span><span data-preserver-spaces="true">on</span><span data-preserver-spaces="true"> five years ago, according to </span><span data-preserver-spaces="true">national</span> <a class="editor-rtfLink" href="https://www.cbs.nl/nl-nl/nieuws/2024/37/percentage-vakbondsleden-onder-werknemers-verder-gedaald" rel="noopener" target="_blank"><span data-preserver-spaces="true">statistics agency CBS</span></a><span data-preserver-spaces="true"> and research institute TNO. </span></p><p><span data-preserver-spaces="true">The biggest decline is among the over 55s. Five years ago, 31% of older workers were a union member, but this has now gone down to 25%. </span></p><p><span data-preserver-spaces="true">There are, however, major differences between the sectors. Some 27% of civil servants and 25% of teachers, for example, are union members but membership is minimal among hospitality industry workers and farm workers – sectors with a long tradition of casual or temporary work. </span></p><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden p-4 bg-light my-8 d-none d-md-block"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Inarticle"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_inarticle" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden p-4 bg-light my-8 d-block d-md-none"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Inarticle"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_inarticle-m" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><p><span data-preserver-spaces="true">In total, 1.4 million people are still members of a trade union, down from 1.9 million 20 years ago. </span></p><p><span data-preserver-spaces="true">The Netherlands has three main trade union groupings, the FNV, CNV </span><span data-preserver-spaces="true">and</span><span data-preserver-spaces="true"> the MHP. </span></p></main><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden d-none d-md-block p-4 bg-light mt-8 mb-10 mx-lg-4"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Native"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_native" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden d-block d-md-none bg-light my-8"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Native"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_native-m" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><footer class="my-8 px-4"><div class="pb-8"></div> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/uncategorized/?list"></a></footer><div class="bg-green-light p-3 mx-4 mt-8 mb-12"></div></article>]]></description><guid>https://www.dutchnews.nl/?p=240547</guid><pubDate>Mon, 09 Sep 2024 07:04:58 -0000</pubDate><dc:creator><![CDATA[Robin Pascoe]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Cooler days ahead and more rain, but next weekend will be dry</title><link>https://www.dutchnews.nl/2024/09/cooler-days-ahead-and-more-rain-but-next-weekend-will-be-dry/</link><description><![CDATA[<article class="post-240545 post type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-society category-weather"><header class="pb-4 px-4"><h1 class="text-serif lh-1"> Cooler days ahead and more rain, but next weekend will be dry</h1> <time class="text-secondary updated me-2" datetime="2024-09-09T06:48:00+00:00"> September 9, 2024 </time></header><figure aria-describedby="caption-attachment-142016" class="px-lg-5" id="attachment_142016"> <img alt="" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" decoding="async" fetchpriority="high" height="424" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px" src="/wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Rain-summer.jpg" srcset="/wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Rain-summer.jpg 600w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Rain-summer-560x396.jpg 560w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Rain-summer-88x62.jpg 88w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Rain-summer-130x92.jpg 130w" width="600"/><figcaption class="px-4 px-lg-0" id="caption-attachment-142016"> Photo: Odi Busman</figcaption></figure><main class="px-4"><p>There is a sharp shift in the weather in the Netherlands this week after the warm weekend, with cooler temperatures and more rain, weather forecasters say.</p><p>Monday will start cloudy with some rain in the south, but the sun will break through in northern parts of the country. The maximum temperature will be around 21°, weather bureau KNMI said.</p><p>Tuesday will be similar, but a couple of degrees colder, and by Wednesday the temperature will be no higher than 15°. Rain will continue all week, but will tail off by Saturday when it will be a little warmer again. Sunday too will be dry, with temperatures around 20°.</p><p>The KNMI’s long-term forecast sees little change towards the end of the month, with temperatures around 20°, some sunny spells and little rain.</p></main><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden d-none d-md-block p-4 bg-light mt-8 mb-10 mx-lg-4"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Native"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_native" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden d-block d-md-none bg-light my-8"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Native"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_native-m" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><footer class="my-8 px-4"><div class="pb-8"></div> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/society/?list"></a> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/weather/?list"></a></footer><div class="bg-green-light p-3 mx-4 mt-8 mb-12"></div></article>]]></description><guid>https://www.dutchnews.nl/?p=240545</guid><pubDate>Mon, 09 Sep 2024 06:48:00 -0000</pubDate><dc:creator><![CDATA[Robin Pascoe]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Commuters face public transport strikes on Tuesday, Wednesday</title><link>https://www.dutchnews.nl/2024/09/commuters-face-public-transport-strikes-on-tuesday-wednesday/</link><description><![CDATA[<article class="post-240542 post type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-public-transport category-retirement category-society category-strikes"><header class="pb-4 px-4"><h1 class="text-serif lh-1"> Commuters face public transport strikes on Tuesday, Wednesday</h1> <time class="text-secondary updated me-2" datetime="2024-09-09T06:20:39+00:00"> September 9, 2024 </time></header><figure aria-describedby="caption-attachment-217722" class="px-lg-5" id="attachment_217722"> <img alt="" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" decoding="async" fetchpriority="high" height="1512" sizes="(max-width: 2016px) 100vw, 2016px" src="/wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/IMG_3068.jpg" srcset="/wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/IMG_3068.jpg 2016w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/IMG_3068-560x420.jpg 560w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/IMG_3068-1200x900.jpg 1200w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/IMG_3068-768x576.jpg 768w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/IMG_3068-1536x1152.jpg 1536w" width="2016"/><figcaption class="px-4 px-lg-0" id="caption-attachment-217722"> Photo: Dutch News</figcaption></figure><main class="px-4"><p><span data-preserver-spaces="true">Commuters </span><span data-preserver-spaces="true">will</span><span data-preserver-spaces="true"> be hit by </span><span data-preserver-spaces="true">major</span><span data-preserver-spaces="true"> problems getting to work on Tuesday and </span><span data-preserver-spaces="true">Wednesday,</span><span data-preserver-spaces="true"> as public transport workers go on strike in support of their early retirement campaign. </span></p><p><span data-preserver-spaces="true">On Tuesday, public transport in Amsterdam, Rotterdam </span><span data-preserver-spaces="true">and</span><span data-preserver-spaces="true"> The Hague will </span><span data-preserver-spaces="true">come to a</span><span data-preserver-spaces="true"> halt between 4 am and 8 am, and on Wednesday, NS and regional transport workers will strike </span><span data-preserver-spaces="true">at the same time</span><span data-preserver-spaces="true">.</span></p><p><span data-preserver-spaces="true">Public transport firms expect it will be around 8.30 </span><span data-preserver-spaces="true">by the time</span><span data-preserver-spaces="true"> services get back to normal after the strikes, but say it could be later before buses, trams </span><span data-preserver-spaces="true">and</span><span data-preserver-spaces="true"> trains are operating according to the timetable.  </span></p><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden p-4 bg-light my-8 d-none d-md-block"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Inarticle"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_inarticle" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden p-4 bg-light my-8 d-block d-md-none"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Inarticle"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_inarticle-m" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><p><span data-preserver-spaces="true">The strikes are part of a series of </span><span data-preserver-spaces="true">stoppages by unions</span><span data-preserver-spaces="true"> in support of a new early retirement scheme for workers in physically taxing jobs. The current ruling is due to expire at the end of this year. The retirement age in the Netherlands is 67.<br/> </span></p><p><span data-preserver-spaces="true">Strikes will follow this week in Rotterdam port, in the construction sector, healthcare </span><span data-preserver-spaces="true">and</span><span data-preserver-spaces="true"> various</span><span data-preserver-spaces="true"> other heavy industries.</span><span data-preserver-spaces="true"> On Monday afternoon, the cleaning sector will </span><span data-preserver-spaces="true">go on</span><span data-preserver-spaces="true"> strike and hold a rally at Schiphol airport. The police have been </span><a class="editor-rtfLink" href="https://www.dutchnews.nl/2024/09/police-to-boycott-ajax-utrecht-match-as-early-retirement-protest/" rel="noopener" target="_blank"><span data-preserver-spaces="true">taking action</span></a><span data-preserver-spaces="true"> since the spring. </span></p><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden p-4 bg-light my-8 d-none d-md-block"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Incontent"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_incontent" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden p-4 bg-light my-8 d-block d-md-none"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Incontent"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_incontent-m" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><p><span data-preserver-spaces="true">Social </span><span data-preserver-spaces="true">affairs minister</span><span data-preserver-spaces="true"> Eddy van Hijum has said he is </span><span data-preserver-spaces="true">looking at</span><span data-preserver-spaces="true"> extending the current regulations and that some cash is available. However, the unions say they are not convinced. </span></p><p><span data-preserver-spaces="true">The </span><a class="editor-rtfLink" href="https://www.dutchnews.nl/2023/05/senators-back-new-pension-system-switch-will-take-4-5-years/" rel="noopener" target="_blank"><span data-preserver-spaces="true">new pension agreement</span></a><span data-preserver-spaces="true"> includes a commitment to a permanent ruling for people in taxing professions </span><span data-preserver-spaces="true">but we</span><span data-preserver-spaces="true"> still don’t have one, Henri Janssen from the FNV-affiliated railway union said. “So we are taking action.” </span></p></main><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden d-none d-md-block p-4 bg-light mt-8 mb-10 mx-lg-4"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Native"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_native" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden d-block d-md-none bg-light my-8"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Native"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_native-m" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><footer class="my-8 px-4"><div class="pb-8"></div> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/public-transport/?list"></a> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/retirement/?list"></a> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/society/?list"></a> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/strikes/?list"></a></footer><div class="bg-green-light p-3 mx-4 mt-8 mb-12"></div></article>]]></description><guid>https://www.dutchnews.nl/?p=240542</guid><pubDate>Mon, 09 Sep 2024 06:20:39 -0000</pubDate><dc:creator><![CDATA[Robin Pascoe]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>“Serious imbalance”: ordinary people pay more tax than the rich</title><link>https://www.dutchnews.nl/2024/09/serious-imbalance-ordinary-people-pay-more-tax-than-the-rich/</link><description><![CDATA[<article class="post-240538 post type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-economy category-tax"><header class="pb-4 px-4"><h1 class="text-serif lh-1"> “Serious imbalance”: ordinary people pay more tax than the rich</h1> <time class="text-secondary updated me-2" datetime="2024-09-09T06:04:40+00:00"> September 9, 2024 </time> <a class="me-2" href="https://www.dutchnews.nl/author/claudia/" rel="author"> Claudia Delpero </a></header><figure aria-describedby="caption-attachment-178218" class="px-lg-5" id="attachment_178218"> <img alt="" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" decoding="async" fetchpriority="high" height="464" sizes="(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px" src="/wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/IMG_6911.jpg" srcset="/wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/IMG_6911.jpg 640w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/IMG_6911-560x406.jpg 560w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/IMG_6911-86x62.jpg 86w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/IMG_6911-130x94.jpg 130w" width="640"/><figcaption class="px-4 px-lg-0" id="caption-attachment-178218"> Photo: DutchNews.nl</figcaption></figure><main class="px-4"><p>Taxation in the Netherlands and across Europe suffers from a “serious imbalance” because taxes on wages and consumption (VAT) raise much more for the public coffers than taxes on wealth and corporations, poverty charity Oxfam has said.</p><p>Analysing data from the European Commission and the EU statistical office Eurostat, Oxfam said that in the Netherlands, taxes on consumption and labour account for more than 76% of total fiscal revenues (€105 billion and €176 billion respectively).</p><p>This contrasts with less than 19% from taxes on capital income (€70 billion), such as corporate tax, and self-employed social contributions.</p><p>Less than 5% of fiscal revenues (€17 billion) come from the taxation of assets, such as taxes on land and buildings or professional and business licences.</p><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden p-4 bg-light my-8 d-none d-md-block"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Inarticle"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_inarticle" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden p-4 bg-light my-8 d-block d-md-none"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Inarticle"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_inarticle-m" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><p>“Our analysis shows that the Netherlands faces a serious tax imbalance,” said Martin Brehm Christensen, tax and inequality expert at Oxfam Novib. “Taxes on consumption are among the highest in the EU.</p><p>“From 2000 to 2023, the top income tax rate for the richest and biggest corporations dropped, while consumption tax rates increased, placing more of the burden on everyday people and benefiting the wealthiest. This stark imbalance shows an urgent need for reform and wealth taxes must be a priority,” he said.</p><p>Across Europe, the analysis shows, consumption and labour taxes account for almost 78% of the total and bring 13 times more revenue to governments than taxes on wealth.</p><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden p-4 bg-light my-8 d-none d-md-block"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Incontent"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_incontent" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden p-4 bg-light my-8 d-block d-md-none"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Incontent"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_incontent-m" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><p>Oxfam also notes that in Europe tax rates for the richest and largest corporations have decreased in the last decades, while tax rates on consumption and labour increased.</p><p>“Labour and consumption taxes account for a higher proportion of income for ordinary citizens,” Oxfam said. “While wealthy individuals also pay taxes on their work income and consumption, these contribute to a smaller proportion of their overall income.</p><p>“Wealthy people also tend to spend a lower proportion of their income on consumption. This is because a higher proportion of poorer people’s income is used to buy essential goods and services such as food.”</p><p>Oxfam is supporting <a href="https://citizens-initiative.europa.eu/initiatives/details/2023/000006_en">calls</a> for the European Commission to establish a European tax on great wealth. The petition needs to be supported by one million people by October 9 to trigger a formal response.</p><p>Oxfam calculates that a progressive wealth tax up to 5% on the EU’s multi-millionaires and billionaires could generate €286.5 billion each year.</p></main><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden d-none d-md-block p-4 bg-light mt-8 mb-10 mx-lg-4"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Native"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_native" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden d-block d-md-none bg-light my-8"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Native"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_native-m" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><footer class="my-8 px-4"><div class="pb-8"></div> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/economy/?list"></a> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/tax/?list"></a></footer><div class="bg-green-light p-3 mx-4 mt-8 mb-12"></div></article>]]></description><guid>https://www.dutchnews.nl/?p=240538</guid><pubDate>Mon, 09 Sep 2024 06:04:40 -0000</pubDate><dc:creator><![CDATA[Claudia Delpero]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Zirkzee leads charge as Oranje cruise to Nations League victory</title><link>https://www.dutchnews.nl/2024/09/zirkzee-leads-charge-as-oranje-cruise-to-nations-league-victory/</link><description><![CDATA[<article class="post-240531 post type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-football category-sport category-uefa-nations-league"><header class="pb-4 px-4"><h1 class="text-serif lh-1"> Zirkzee leads charge as Oranje cruise to Nations League victory</h1> <time class="text-secondary updated me-2" datetime="2024-09-07T21:04:15+00:00"> September 7, 2024 </time></header><figure aria-describedby="caption-attachment-240532" class="px-lg-5" id="attachment_240532"> <img alt="" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" decoding="async" fetchpriority="high" height="1706" sizes="(max-width: 2560px) 100vw, 2560px" src="/wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/ANP-507907316-scaled.jpg" srcset="/wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/ANP-507907316-scaled.jpg 2560w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/ANP-507907316-560x373.jpg 560w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/ANP-507907316-1200x800.jpg 1200w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/ANP-507907316-360x240.jpg 360w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/ANP-507907316-768x512.jpg 768w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/ANP-507907316-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/ANP-507907316-2048x1365.jpg 2048w" width="2560"/><figcaption class="px-4 px-lg-0" id="caption-attachment-240532"> Goalscorers Joshua Zirkzee, Cody Gakpo and Tijjani Reijnders celebrate after Gakpo scores the third goal. Photo: ANP/Pieter Stam de Jong</figcaption></figure><main class="px-4"><p>The Netherlands opened their Nations League campaign with a comfortable 5-2 win in Eindhoven against Bosnia and Herzegovina.</p><p>Joshua Zirkzee crowned his international debut with the opening goal after just 13 minutes when his header crept inside the post, after a shot by Xavi Simons was diverted into his path.</p><p>The Balkan nation were sparked into action and deservedly equalised when Ermedin Demirovic finished off a crisp passing move with a low shot into the corner.</p><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden p-4 bg-light my-8 d-none d-md-block"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Inarticle"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_inarticle" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden p-4 bg-light my-8 d-block d-md-none"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Inarticle"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_inarticle-m" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><p>But Tijjani Reijnders restored the advantage on the stroke of half-time and Ronald Koeman’s side dominated the second period.</p><p>Cody Gakpo extended the lead from close range after 56 minutes, and though Edin Dzeko gave the Dutch a scare when he turned in a long pass, late goals by Wout Weghorst and Simons ensured a scoreline that was by no means flattering.</p><p>“We were very good in possession, we looked fast and fresh, the players were finding each other between the lines and we had an excellent spell after the break,” Koeman said.</p><p>“You saw a few doubts creep in at 3-2, but that wasn’t the attitude on the pitch. They scored two goals from very little.”</p><p>Oranje’s next match is in Amsterdam on Tuesday against Germany, who beat Hungary 5-0 in their opening game on Saturday.</p></main><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden d-none d-md-block p-4 bg-light mt-8 mb-10 mx-lg-4"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Native"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_native" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden d-block d-md-none bg-light my-8"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Native"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_native-m" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><footer class="my-8 px-4"><div class="pb-8"></div> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/football/?list"></a> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/sport/?list"></a> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/football/uefa-nations-league/?list"></a></footer><div class="bg-green-light p-3 mx-4 mt-8 mb-12"></div></article>]]></description><guid>https://www.dutchnews.nl/?p=240531</guid><pubDate>Sat, 07 Sep 2024 21:04:15 -0000</pubDate><dc:creator><![CDATA[Gordon Darroch]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>One in five Dutch adults live alone, most are elderly women</title><link>https://www.dutchnews.nl/2024/09/one-in-five-dutch-adults-live-alone-most-are-elderly-women/</link><description><![CDATA[<article class="post-240521 post type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-elderly category-society"><header class="pb-4 px-4"><h1 class="text-serif lh-1"> One in five Dutch adults live alone, most are elderly women</h1> <time class="text-secondary updated me-2" datetime="2024-09-07T09:43:28+00:00"> September 7, 2024 </time></header><figure aria-describedby="caption-attachment-240522" class="px-lg-5" id="attachment_240522"> <img alt="" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" decoding="async" fetchpriority="high" height="707" sizes="(max-width: 1000px) 100vw, 1000px" src="/wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/Depositphotos_5190419_S.jpg" srcset="/wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/Depositphotos_5190419_S.jpg 1000w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/Depositphotos_5190419_S-560x396.jpg 560w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/Depositphotos_5190419_S-768x543.jpg 768w" width="1000"/><figcaption class="px-4 px-lg-0" id="caption-attachment-240522"> Photo: Depositphotos.com</figcaption></figure><main class="px-4"><p>Some 3.3 million of the Netherlands’ population of 18 million live alone, or almost one in five people, according to calculations by <a href="https://www.cbs.nl/nl-nl/nieuws/2024/36/1-op-de-5-mensen-woont-alleen">national statistics agency CBS.</a></p><p>Most of those living alone are women over the age 70, many of whose partner has died. At the beginning of this year, 613,000 elderly women lived by themselves, compared with 274,000 older men.</p><p>Slightly more men than women in their 20s live alone and by the time they reach 30 and 40, men are clearly in the majority, the CBS said. That is partly down to divorce and children remaining with their mother.</p><p>In 1960, just 3% of the population lived alone, and the percentage has increased steadily since then. By the mid 1980s, the total had topped 10%, reaching 19% at the beginning of this year.</p></main><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden d-none d-md-block p-4 bg-light mt-8 mb-10 mx-lg-4"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Native"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_native" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden d-block d-md-none bg-light my-8"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Native"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_native-m" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><footer class="my-8 px-4"><div class="pb-8"></div> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/elderly/?list"></a> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/society/?list"></a></footer><div class="bg-green-light p-3 mx-4 mt-8 mb-12"></div></article>]]></description><guid>https://www.dutchnews.nl/?p=240521</guid><pubDate>Sat, 07 Sep 2024 09:43:28 -0000</pubDate><dc:creator><![CDATA[Robin Pascoe]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>WeTransfer’s new owner plans to slash workforce up to 75%: FD</title><link>https://www.dutchnews.nl/2024/09/wetransfers-new-owner-plans-to-slash-workforce-up-to-75-fd/</link><description><![CDATA[<article class="post-240518 post type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-business category-economy category-jobs category-tech"><header class="pb-4 px-4"><h1 class="text-serif lh-1"> WeTransfer’s new owner plans to slash workforce up to 75%: FD</h1> <time class="text-secondary updated me-2" datetime="2024-09-07T09:18:40+00:00"> September 7, 2024 </time></header><figure aria-describedby="caption-attachment-181541" class="px-lg-5" id="attachment_181541"> <img alt="" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" decoding="async" fetchpriority="high" height="667" sizes="(max-width: 1000px) 100vw, 1000px" src="/wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/Depositphotos_13159839_s-2019-1.jpg" srcset="/wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/Depositphotos_13159839_s-2019-1.jpg 1000w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/Depositphotos_13159839_s-2019-1-560x374.jpg 560w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/Depositphotos_13159839_s-2019-1-360x240.jpg 360w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/Depositphotos_13159839_s-2019-1-768x512.jpg 768w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/Depositphotos_13159839_s-2019-1-640x427.jpg 640w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/Depositphotos_13159839_s-2019-1-92x62.jpg 92w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/Depositphotos_13159839_s-2019-1-130x87.jpg 130w" width="1000"/></figure><main class="px-4"><p>The new owner of Dutch file transfer service WeTransfer is planning to cut “up to 75%” of the workforce, the <a href="https://fd.nl/tech-en-innovatie/1530090/italiaanse-eigenaar-schrapt-tot-driekwart-banen-wetransfer-een-maand-na-overname">Financieele</a> Dagblad reported on Saturday.</p><p>In total, some 260 jobs will go, company sources told the paper and staff were given the shock news at the company’s Amsterdam operations on Friday. WeTransfer has a workforce of 350 people.</p><p>Italian firm Bending Spoons <a href="https://www.dutchnews.nl/2024/08/dutch-file-sharing-service-wetransfer-goes-italian/">took over the company</a> a month ago and financial details were not disclosed. WeTransfer booked <span data-preserver-spaces="true">turnover</span><span data-preserver-spaces="true"> of €132 million last year but net profit fell 60% to just under €11 million.</span></p><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden p-4 bg-light my-8 d-none d-md-block"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Inarticle"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_inarticle" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden p-4 bg-light my-8 d-block d-md-none"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Inarticle"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_inarticle-m" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><p>Bending Spoons chief executive Luca Ferrari is reported to have said the company will function better if it is “smaller and more focused”.</p><p>WeTransfer claims to have some 80 million active users and 600,000 subscribers. Around half its income comes from advertising, the rest from paid services.</p></main><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden d-none d-md-block p-4 bg-light mt-8 mb-10 mx-lg-4"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Native"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_native" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden d-block d-md-none bg-light my-8"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Native"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_native-m" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><footer class="my-8 px-4"><div class="pb-8"></div> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/business/?list"></a> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/economy/?list"></a> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/jobs/?list"></a> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/tech/?list"></a></footer><div class="bg-green-light p-3 mx-4 mt-8 mb-12"></div></article>]]></description><guid>https://www.dutchnews.nl/?p=240518</guid><pubDate>Sat, 07 Sep 2024 09:18:40 -0000</pubDate><dc:creator><![CDATA[Robin Pascoe]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Ice rink introduces compulsory helmets after rise in injuries</title><link>https://www.dutchnews.nl/2024/09/ice-rink-introduces-compulsory-helmets-after-rise-in-injuries/</link><description><![CDATA[<article class="post-240514 post type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-accidents category-skating category-sport"><header class="pb-4 px-4"><h1 class="text-serif lh-1"> Ice rink introduces compulsory helmets after rise in injuries</h1> <time class="text-secondary updated me-2" datetime="2024-09-07T08:56:54+00:00"> September 7, 2024 </time></header><figure aria-describedby="caption-attachment-240515" class="px-lg-5" id="attachment_240515"> <img alt="" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" decoding="async" fetchpriority="high" height="1706" sizes="(max-width: 2560px) 100vw, 2560px" src="/wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/Depositphotos_228842270_XL-scaled.jpg" srcset="/wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/Depositphotos_228842270_XL-scaled.jpg 2560w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/Depositphotos_228842270_XL-560x373.jpg 560w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/Depositphotos_228842270_XL-1200x800.jpg 1200w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/Depositphotos_228842270_XL-360x240.jpg 360w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/Depositphotos_228842270_XL-768x512.jpg 768w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/Depositphotos_228842270_XL-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/Depositphotos_228842270_XL-2048x1365.jpg 2048w" width="2560"/><figcaption class="px-4 px-lg-0" id="caption-attachment-240515"> Photo: Depositphotos.com</figcaption></figure><main class="px-4"><p>The debate about helmets for cyclists may be raging in the Netherlands, but the Thialf ice rink in Heerenveen has taken the plunge and introduced compulsory head protection for skaters.</p><p>The requirement has been introduced because of “an increase in the number of incidents causing considerable injury”, the rink said in an update of its rules.</p><p>Most skaters welcome the use of helmets, director Minne Dolsta told local broadcaster <a href="https://www.omropfryslan.nl/nl/nieuws/16808306/thialf-voert-helmplicht-in-vanwege-toenemend-aantal-incidenten">Omrop Fryslân</a>. “More and more skating clubs are making helmets compulsory and we’ve noticed <a href="https://nos.nl/artikel/2499172-helm-raakt-steeds-meer-ingeburgerd-op-de-schaatsbaan">more people</a> just coming to skate wearing them.”</p><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden p-4 bg-light my-8 d-none d-md-block"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Inarticle"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_inarticle" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden p-4 bg-light my-8 d-block d-md-none"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Inarticle"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_inarticle-m" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><p>The rules won’t apply to professionals, although helmets have been a requirement in short track, marathons and the mass start events in the Netherlands for years. Helmets are also worn in ISU team sprint and team pursuit events.</p><p>The Dutch skating association has welcomed the Thialf move, which will come into effect on September 23, when the new season starts.</p></main><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden d-none d-md-block p-4 bg-light mt-8 mb-10 mx-lg-4"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Native"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_native" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden d-block d-md-none bg-light my-8"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Native"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_native-m" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><footer class="my-8 px-4"><div class="pb-8"></div> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/accidents/?list"></a> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/skating/?list"></a> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/sport/?list"></a></footer><div class="bg-green-light p-3 mx-4 mt-8 mb-12"></div></article>]]></description><guid>https://www.dutchnews.nl/?p=240514</guid><pubDate>Sat, 07 Sep 2024 08:56:54 -0000</pubDate><dc:creator><![CDATA[Robin Pascoe]]></dc:creator></item></channel></rss>